    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A series of silicon hydride compounds, analogous to paraffin hydrocarbons, and having the general formula (Si)n(H2)n+2. Silanes are inherently unstable but have the unique ability to bind organic polymers to inorganic substrates. They have been used in the consolidation of masonry, adobe, and stone. </Note_Text>
